{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"fields":{"description":"# Realign rebar reviews to the three-pass (evidence -> binary-verify -> deterministic-gate) structure\n\n## Context\nIndustry practice and 2025-2026 research converge: an LLM reviewer should surface cited evidence against a locked rubric; a SEPARATE agent should validate each finding via atomic binary sub-questions; and a DETERMINISTIC policy (not the model) should decide severity and blocking. LLMs are unreliable at holistic severity/confidence judgments, so neither is emitted by the model. This epic builds that shared three-pass framework and migrates rebar's existing reviewers onto it.\n\n## Prerequisite foundations — current codebase state (2026-06)\n\nFoundations shipped since this epic was written; the design is UNCHANGED, but the substrate is now CONCRETE for\nparts and the reviewer migration is PARTLY done (the closed prerequisite epics are NOT reopened — this realigns\nTHIS epic to what they delivered):\n\n- **Reviewer PROMPT migration DONE; three-pass STRUCTURE migration still pending (epic `da27`, closed).** The\n  existing reviewers (`code_quality`/`security`/`tests`/`spec_alignment`/`ticket_quality`/`completion_verifier`)\n  were migrated to the front-matter CONTRACT model — `inputs`/`outputs` schema-name contracts, `execution_mode`,\n  `dimension`, `applies_to` globs, a derived index + CI drift gate (`src/rebar/llm/prompts.py`, `reviewers/*.md`).\n  That is the PROMPT-STORAGE half of 'migrate existing reviewers'. They still emit the OLD pass-1 shape\n  `{findings:[{severity, dimension, detail, citations}], summary}`, NOT this epic's pass-1 EVIDENCE contract\n  `{finding, criteria[], evidence[], scenarios[], impact}` — migrating the pass-1 SHAPE + adding Pass-2/Pass-3 is\n  THIS epic's remaining work, layered on the already-contracted prompts.\n- **Pass-1 data substrate (partial) + single-pass `review_code`.** `src/rebar/llm/findings.py`\n  (`normalize_finding`, citation coercion, schema validation) + `src/rebar/llm/aggregate.py` (cluster +\n  severity×agreement rank) exist; `review_code` (`src/rebar/llm/code_review.py`) runs reviewers + aggregates today\n  as a SINGLE PASS. There is NO Pass-2 verifier agent and NO Pass-3 deterministic gate yet — both are NEW WORK here.\n- **Provider-agnostic runner + workflow engine (epic `e6d9`, closed).** `PydanticAIRunner` (`src/rebar/llm/runner.py`)\n  is the sole runtime (LangGraph cut over), honoring the `execution_mode` {single_turn|agentic} seam — the substrate\n  Pass-1 and the separate-context Pass-2 verifier run on; the declarative workflow engine (`run_workflow`) + the\n  Inspect-AI eval seam shipped alongside.\n- **Code-grounding for Pass-2 (epic `8f6c`, closed).** `src/rebar/grounding/` (the `refute_absence`/`applies`/`scan`\n  facade, exported from `src/rebar/grounding/__init__.py`) is the substrate for Pass-2's RE-GROUNDING in the actual\n  code + the cited-code-reference-accuracy VETO. The overlay catalogs' 'Scanner pre-pass (Semgrep/Gitleaks/Trivy)'\n  maps to the oracle's EXTENSIBLE detector registry (`detectors/registry.py`; OpenGrep/ast-grep shipped) — but\n  security/secrets/CVE detectors are NOT yet shipped (only `smell_generic` + applicability), so those remain new\n  work (here or shared with the code-review capability epic `b744`).\n\n## Success Criteria\n- All rebar reviews emit the pass-1 evidence contract; a shared pass-2 verifier agent and pass-3 deterministic aggregator exist and are used.\n- Severity is computed deterministically from structured attributes; validity/confidence from typed binary sub-answers. No model-emitted severity number, confidence number, or high/med/low rating in the decision path.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Pass-1 finding contract: `{finding (free text), criteria[] (each in the prompt's locked rubric set), evidence[] (flexible free text: code citations, prose, OR absence rationale), scenarios[] (free text), impact (free text)}`. Criteria is an array. No model severity/confidence.\n- [ ] Pass-2 verifier = a separate agent / independent context that re-grounds in the actual code (via the shipped 8f6c grounding-oracle facade `refute_absence`/`scan` for cited-reference + smell grounding) and emits per finding: (a) severity attributes `{prod_impact, debt_impact, blast_radius, likelihood, reversibility}` (coarse ordinals); (b) typed binary sub-answers `{verdict: yes|no|insufficient, evidence_span/reason}`.\n- [ ] Binary sub-question set (typed): the ONLY veto is cited-code-reference-accuracy, applied ONLY when a code citation is present (no-op for absence findings / non-code reviews); all others GRADED: is-verifiable (signal), evidence-entails-finding, path-reachable, impact-follows-necessarily, no-viable-alternative-explanation, no-existing-mitigation, severity-claim-justified.\n- [ ] Pass-3 deterministic aggregator: conditional veto gate -> graded confidence (weighted fraction / log-odds) -> severity-from-attributes -> `block | advisory` against per-criteria thresholds (project-overridable; defaults start high -> almost all findings advisory while calibration data is gathered). No interactive escalation path (autonomous).\n- [ ] Verifier prompt obeys the research rules: atomicity (one proposition per question); independence (do not show the finding's own conclusion when answering each sub-question); verdict-with-citation, NOT verdict-with-proposed-fix; allow \"insufficient\".\n- [ ] Existing code-review reviewers (review_ticket and the code-quality/security/tests reviewers) migrated to the pass-1 EVIDENCE contract + shared pass-2/pass-3 — these are ALREADY on the da27 front-matter CONTRACT model (inputs/outputs/execution_mode/dimension/applies_to + derived index), so this is the pass-1-SHAPE + Pass-2/Pass-3 migration ON TOP of that, NOT a from-scratch reviewer rewrite; findings schema extended (`src/rebar/llm/findings.py`); aggregation + citation-resolution + schema-pin tests updated. (completion_verifier is OUT OF SCOPE: not migrated, unchanged.)\n- [ ] Rubric sourced from Google eng-practices + Anthropic security taxonomy (locked + versioned); Conventional Comments not adopted.\n- [ ] Known limitations recorded: veto-brittleness mitigated by the single conditional veto; decomposition controls validity PRECISION not finding-type RECALL; threshold calibration is explicitly out of scope (separate future work)."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1782271852773285001,"uuid":"824451fb-9026-43f2-9eee-9a10feaed3e2"}